text:
there‚Äôs a myth that counseling is only for ‚Äúserious‚Äù mental instability and ‚Äúcrazy‚Äù people. our society, especially in communities of color, stigmatize counseling as this place where you go tell a total stranger all the secrets, cry all the tears, blame all the people, and stay all messed up. nope! 
counseling is where you find words for the things in your heart that are screaming but mute. it‚Äôs the place where you learn to be curious about your own goodness and worth. it‚Äôs where you practice deep courage and the necessary skills of vulnerability. it‚Äôs nourishment for hungry personal development. it‚Äôs where you scoop all your mental poop and throw it in the trash.
and, it‚Äôs awesome. üíï
i know, i know-  there are good counselors and bad ones - just like cops, teachers, doctors, nurses, and just about all other professionals in life we are supposed to trust. you‚Äôll have to keep looking for the right one- but i‚Äôm confident you‚Äôre worth it.
/
most times i leave counseling puffy eyes exhausted from all the soul work i do in one eternal hour. i find words come easier after i‚Äôve given my tears permission to be seen.
some times i leave invigorated and purely joyful because i‚Äôve just spent time seeing my own beauty, realizing my worth and giving myself permission to be utterly human. /
today is a joyful day.  today i‚Äôm glowing on the inside because i heard and actually believed the wisdom spoken over and to me.
/
listen. i‚Äôve been at this whole trauma/emotional healing journey for many years. i‚Äôve spent lots of money and tons of time working on my own piles of mental poop. i‚Äôve spent even more time learning how to keep other people‚Äôs poop off me! it‚Äôs not a quick process, and sometimes it downright sucks, but.... it. is. worth. it. 
it‚Äôs what cultivates courage so i can share some bravery with others- food, fitness, personal growth, self care, healing and mental poop scooping - all of it! 
#becourageous #traumainformed #traumahealing #metoo #emotionalintelligence #ptsdrecovery #complexptsd #anxiety #healing #intentionalliving #mystorymatters

text_retweet:
the greatest truth...and hardest to swallow. even in this day and age, the "prince charming" syndrome exist. the idea that someone else can fix your situation. but the fact is....they can't. you have to own it, accept it, acknowledge it...-you- have to do the (proverbial) dirty work to change your reality.  it's like the old joke "how many psychiatrist does it take to change a light bulb? one, but the lightbulb has to really want to change!". quotes, books, posts, doctors, counsellors...all can give advice, inspire you, point you in the right direction...but only you can do the work, fight your demons, persevere, grow and move forward. the hardest part...is looking in the mirror and being brutally honest with yourself. taking responsibility...owning it...and then honestly working on it. but it will be the most rewarding battle of your life. to stand on your own two feet, head held high and be whole in yourself. able to face the storm...and not bow.  to look in the mirror...and find peace. to face your demons and take their power away. grow your self love,  nurture your growth,  invest in your confidence. you are capable and worthy.

text:
had to post an obligatory bathroom #selfie from the #holidayparty last night. love this @hm suit and @katespadeny hat. üéÑ

i will say i was incredibly upset with the @airzoo_ though. i was excited to bring my daughter with me, since she loved the air zoo and the rides. and now that she is 48‚Äù tall (per her doctor) she was finally tall enough to ride the flight simulator. she was so excited!!! we waited in the long line but then the guys running the ride wouldn‚Äôt let her on. her hair style was a problem for them because it was on top of her head. and then they were telling her she had to take off her boots (flats that she wears to school everyday) to check to ride (though that is not their standard protocol. i‚Äôve watched during previous visits). she was tall enough per their ruler (swipe ‚û°Ô∏è to see) and the manager agreed that she was tall enough to ride but then we were told ‚Äúit was at the operators discretion.‚Äù so, they all admitted that she hit the line on their ruler, but they weren‚Äôt going to let her on. and then my once excited daughter was standing there in tears because they were basically #bullying her. i did not let her take off her boots or her hair down because to be honest in a world of #metoo and with a kid who takes everything so literally, the last thing i want to (or can) teach my young daughter is that when a man (or group of men in this case) tell you to take any item off, you have to or that you have to change your hairstyle. needless to say, what had been a fun night ended with a heartbroken kid and a mad mom. #harassment sure does start young these days. merry christmas to you too #airzoo. #grinch. ‚úàÔ∏èüò°

every 98 seconds an american is sexually assualted. as of 1998, an estimated 17.7 million american women had been victims of attempted or completed rape. that's only americas statistics.. based on the available data, 21.8% of american rapes of female victims are¬†gang rapes.. 1 in 10 women have been raped by an intimate partner. gun violence, killings, beatings, domestic abuse etc are real issues. these victims matter, their stories matter, their voice matters, and in cases of murder their lives and memory matter! these random facts are just a small percentage of facts that can be presented other examples include the backlogging rape cases and laws that need to be repealed and replaced. to any and all the victims of #metoo movement and all those who have yet to tell their story or couldn't i want you to know you are loved and please stay strong. if you need help please ask. never be afraid of those that judge. those that judge will be judged in their time. you are beautiful and you deserve to be free of your secret,pain, and past! i think so often of my bubbe (may she rest in peace) and how strong she was to be a survivor. she was raped at gunpoint and yet it never defined her. she rose above. she fought the demons #baruchhashem so can you! this isn't a post about likes but a post about awareness.  #lovepeoplemore #love #xo #womenmatter #domesticabuse #guncontrol #processrapekits #jewishwomen #changelawsthathurtwomen #women #womeninthe21stcentury #jewishgirlsrock

text: when i was 7, i had acting and #elocution lessons to talk proper. it was tough because i had a problem with pronouncing -ths and my teacher wasn‚Äôt very nice (she came from the upper middle-class and i was a child of a nurse & a policeman)..she was a bit ‚Äòsniffy‚Äô with me!!) or perhaps i just was an annoying precocious  brat?! üòÇ the first comedian/actor/ famous person i ever met- as a kid- was ronniecorbett- i waited outside the #tworonnies stage door for what felt like hours until the little ronnie came out. he asked me what i wanted to be when i grew up and i said, without a beat, ‚Äòan actress‚Äô ( i didn‚Äôt know i was #intersex for another 16 years). ronnie said, ‚Äòoh don‚Äôt do that, it‚Äôs very hard to get work‚Äô. i was a little crestfallen but resolute- ‚Äôi can do it!‚Äô my acting career ended aged 14 when i went from being caterpillar the year before to cinderella (because the 30-something male director had decided i was going to be his girlfriend (literally). his had a wife but she was ‚Äòlike my mother‚Äô. funnily enough after i ‚Äòlost my virginity‚Äô to him- aged late 14, maybe 15- i was too high by now to remember much- i forgot i wanted to act. now aged 49- i just got my first ever paid role. thank you @iisuperwomanii for making my dream come true. üåà and huge thanks to @anthonymeindl @amawstudios & my acting tutor @katelinchesna & stand-up tutors @danikleinmodisett & @logan_murray_comedy_guru & + improv training @thegroundlings  #miracles happen in #recovery #metoo #newhollywood @gaptoofentertainment @rivergallo @tildacanyouhearme @sadecjoseph

text: so there are #metoo accusations against neil degrasse tyson, and i don't find it surprising, i stopped listening a while ago because he talks over his female guests. then michiou kaku came out to support ndt. problem is, physics isn't social science, and michiou also repeatedly talks over female guests, especially if they disagree with him and try to bring some actual science in the room to counter his "everything sci-fi is real, because quantum physics!" malarky. that, and sexism and misogyny is rampant in ther sciences, and it pisses me off. and people who should be good people, use their smarts to explain away shitty behaviour. it's so gaslighty and not actually a morally defensible position. i vented about it, and picked up this dingleberry. since "for your consideration" season has started, i leave this little gift to you. i hope you have as much fun reading it as i did arguing.
